jcr:content.jcr:description: Introducing Jacky Hunt-Broersma, ultramarathoner, mother, and cancer survivor. Learn more about her running career and journey to run 100 marathons in 100 days.
jcr:content.jcr:title: Jacky Hunt-Broersma X Boston Marathon
jcr:content.pageTitle: Jacky Hunt-Broersma—100 Marathons in 100 Days. | Altra Running

text_copy_copy_copy.text:
Jacky Hunt-Broersma is the epitome of “Run Without Rules.” The cancer survivor and mother is one of the most accomplished amputee ultramarathoners around, trailblazing firsts for all female and amputee runners.

 

After losing her leg to cancer, Jacky’s running journey began. From there, she has found her stride in the 50-mile race length. Her running career is crowned with accomplishments like breaking World Records, being named WRAL Athlete of the Year, and being named Strong Fitness Magazine’s Woman to Watch in 2021. She is also the first amputee runner to take on the TransRockies Mountain Stage trail race and the The Naturalist 25k trail race.

 

04-28-2022

video.description: Jacky Hunt-Broersma takes on the Boston Marathon on her way to the world record of 102 marathons in 102 days.
video.name: Jacky Hunt X Boston Marathon

text_copy.text: Currently, Jacky is on her way to running 102 marathons in 102 days, with the goal of breaking the World Record for running a marathon every day. The Boston Marathon marked marathon number 92 for her on this journey. During this time, she will be raising money for Amputee Blade Runners—a charity that provides blades for amputees like her.
